
In this problem we consider a Bayesian model with observations $x_1,\ldots,x_n$ iid $(x_i \,\vline\, \mu,\phi) \sim $N$(\mu, \frac{1}{\phi})$.\todo{variance or standard deviation?}  In sections A.1 through A.5 we adopt a prior where $\mu \sim$N$(0,1)$ and $\phi\sim$Gamma$(1,2)$ are independent.
